race.description: Gerry Brown's Shelving And Storage Handicap (Bm60)
race.comment: OKESUTORA (1) improved again leading and winning a 70 over this trip at the Sunshine Coast and then disappointed when well supported at Eagle Farm. Was found to have mild heat stress which may explain. Is back after 10 days and gets in well with the 2kg claim. Tough to beat in this grade. FLYING CELICA (6) brings threatening form over a mile. The extra meters are a slight niggle, but she's in good form and arrives on a 7-day backup. MAZITA (2) made sharp improvement placing over a mile at Ipswich. She'd be in the money holding that form. MARAVICH (5) usually races handy but settled off the pace and was caught wide at Ipswich. Was a big Maiden winner over a mile at Beaudesert prior, and that level of form would have him around the mark. SIR GOLDALOT (3) found a 68 a bit tough last time and was plain the one prior. The form leading into those suggested he was close to another win. No surprise to see him go better.
